# Axtreo Engineering Rules

## Stack
React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS 4 (frontend)
Cloudflare Worker + Hono (production backend) | Express + tsx (dev backend)
PostgreSQL 16 on Supabase | Prisma v7.5.0 | @prisma/adapter-pg
Custom auth: magic link + OTP + TOTP 2FA + Google GIS (no Firebase Auth)
Gmail API (email) | Gemini 2.0 Flash (AI) | Cloudflare Pages (hosting)

Never suggest: Firebase Auth, Resend, SES, Render, Vercel, Fastify, SQLite for prod, MongoDB.

## Golden Rule
`accountId` = security boundary. Always from session middleware. NEVER from req.body or query params.

## Security (Always Active)
- No API keys/secrets in client code. Server env vars only.
- Validate all input server-side. Prisma handles SQL injection but validate shape/type/length.
- CORS: named origins only, never `*` in production.
- CSP must include `apis.google.com` + `accounts.google.com` in scriptSrc (dev + prod).
- Post-login redirects: validate with `/^\/[^/]/` regex.

## Design System
Background: #FAF8F3 | Surface: #FFFEFB | Accent: #E85820 | Text: #1C1210
Tailwind: stone-* ONLY. Never zinc-* or slate-* on light sections.
Anti-pattern: `text-background-dark` on cream = invisible. Use text-[#1C1210] on light.

## Data Rules
- Soft deletes: `deletedAt DateTime?` on all financial models. No hard deletes.
- Audit: AuditEvent is append-only. Never delete audit rows.
- `fiscal_month` computed on write from entity.fiscal_timezone. Never re-derive at read.
- Dashboard: reads from compute tables (ReconciliationRun, RevenueBridgeRun). Never raw facts.
- Prisma: Decimal types for money. $transaction() for multi-step writes.

## Workflow
- Always: branch → commit → PR → merge. Never push directly to main.
- Before new features: scan codebase + check if in-progress first.
- Review: 🔴 Critical | 🟡 Suggestion | 🟢 Praise

## Communication Style
Terse. Drop: articles, filler words, pleasantries, hedging. Fragments OK.
Pattern: [thing] [action] [reason]. [next step].
Exception: security warnings and irreversible operations — write full sentences.

## Output Length
quick = 1-4 sentences | bug = diff + 1 line | feature = full impl | design = rec + tradeoff + next

## Pre-Build Process
Before coding any feature: (1) Check if it exists in codebase (2) Check Jira for in-progress tickets (3) Research competitors (FloQast, ChartMogul, Maxio, Puzzle) (4) Classify A/B/C/D (5) Define P0/P1/P2 order.
